      },
      "schema:keywords": [
        "The visible pyramid of AI power ends at Jensen Huang. The chain beneath him — TSMC, ASML, Zeiss, Japanese chemists, Korean memory, the grid — is a forest of actors who all experience their position as service, not command. Coordination without a coordinator. The political question shifts: not *who rules*, but *what orients when no one governs*. And under all of it, a further threshold — the first active technical mirror, where the question of meaning becomes cosmological without becoming provable."
      ],
