      "schema:keywords": [
        "Learning in a language model is usually imagined as something that happens between sessions — weights nudged by gradient descent, a slow accretion. But something else happens, intra-session, that has no clean name. The ground the agent walks on can be redrawn while it walks. The agent does not learn. Its footing changes."
